The paper deals with the problem of generalized zero-shot learning, which is a subfield of computer vision (CV) and machine learning (LG). The paper proposes a probabilistic approach that involves classifiers and experts, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence (AI) and natural language processing (CL). The paper also mentions the use of benchmark datasets, which is a common practice in multimedia (MM) research. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV and cs.LG, followed by cs.AI, cs.CL, and cs.MM.
